00:01:07.630 --> 00:01:12.540
Actually San Diego county had the same idea,
they’re currently building the biggest desalination

00:01:12.540 --> 00:01:15.579
plant in the western hemisphere to the tune
of 1 billion dollars.

00:01:15.579 --> 00:01:19.979
When it’s finished next year it will make
204 million liters of potable water daily

00:01:19.979 --> 00:01:22.409
and sell at a dollar for every 616 liters.

00:01:22.409 --> 00:01:24.299
Wow, we’re in the clear.

00:01:24.299 --> 00:01:26.109
Eh, not so fast.

00:01:26.109 --> 00:01:28.780
While it sounds like a lot of cheap water,
the opposite is true.

00:01:28.780 --> 00:01:33.580
That price is 80% higher than San Diego pays
for treated water outside the county, and

00:01:33.580 --> 00:01:38.090
even though this plant is huge it can only
make 10% of the county’s needs.

00:01:38.090 --> 00:01:41.920
And it’ll use a lot of energy because it’s
forcing pressurized water through a membrane

00:01:41.920 --> 00:01:45.740
to separate the water from the salt in a process
called reverse osmosis.

00:01:45.740 --> 00:01:49.899
It’s drought-proof and doesn’t rely on
recycling a resource we’re running out of

00:01:49.899 --> 00:01:53.810
but as a practical way to solve California’s
water woes, it’s more of a small puzzle

00:01:53.810 --> 00:01:55.439
piece than the ultimate solution.

00:01:55.439 --> 00:01:59.499
To put it in perspective, there are countries
where water desalination is crucial.

00:01:59.499 --> 00:02:04.609
Israel is one such country, and their desalination
plants provide 35% of their drinking water,

00:02:04.609 --> 00:02:06.899
or enough for 2.8 million people.

00:02:06.899 --> 00:02:11.840
California’s population is 5 times the size
of Israel’s, and the agriculture industry

00:02:11.840 --> 00:02:13.540
is 32 times bigger.

00:02:13.540 --> 00:02:18.100
4 desalination plants may be fine for Israel,
but it’s not enough for the west coast.

00:02:18.100 --> 00:02:19.100
Not by a long shot.

00:02:19.100 --> 00:02:23.700
California also needs water urgently, so focusing
more on conservation and recycling may be

00:02:23.700 --> 00:02:27.680
